---
title: Good Gravy! Pork Chops with Roasted Broccoli and a Sweet Potato and Carrot Mash
description: Goodness gracious! It’s pork like you’ve never experienced it before. These pan-seared chops are drizzled with a creamy honey mustard gravy that will have kids and adults alike licking up every last drop of sweet and savory flavor. And although that rich sauce pairs perfectly with the lean meat, we have a feeling you’ll want to put it on everything, including the roasted broccoli and carrot and sweet potato mash on the side.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/good-gravy-pork-chops-6d6a8cd9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/good-gravy-pork-chops-5b8715e3ae08b546975d7aa2-a8547c83.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/good-gravy-pork-chops-5b8715e3ae08b546975d7aa2
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 41 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 590 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Peel @carrots{6} and @sweet potatoes{2}; cut both into ½-inch cubes.

Place carrots and sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil. Cook until tender, about ~{20%minutes}. Scoop out ¼ cup cooking water, then drain and return cubes to pot.

Meanwhile, toss @broccoli florets{16%ounce} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{} and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until crisp and edges are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. While broccoli roasts, pat @pork chops{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with salt, pepper, and half the @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside on a #plate{} to rest. Wipe out pan. Melt 1 TBSP @butter{5%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-low heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until just softened, about ~{1%minute}. Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @honey{½%ounce}, and ½ cup water. Simmer until reduced, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Reduce heat under pan to low and whisk in 2 TBSP @sour cream{6%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter. Remove from heat. Season gravy with salt, pepper, and remaining paprika. Set aside. Mash carrots and sweet potatoes in pot until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Stir in remaining sour cream and 3 TBSP butter. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If stiff, stir in cooking water 1-2 TBSP at a time until mash is creamy.

Divide broccoli, mash, and pork between plates. Stir any juices released by pork into gravy in pan. Spoon gravy over pork. Sprinkle everything with scallion greens and serve.